    <h1>What is a sitemap?</h1>
        
    <p class="mb-25">
        A sitemaps is a type of file that contains structural information about the pages and content on your website.  
    </p>
    <h2 class="_20">Why do you need a sitemap for your website?</h2>

    <p class="mb-25 _14">
        Sitemaps are used in websites so that search engines and other data collectors can better understand the information and pages on your website. They help them find pages and get a better idea of the structure. 
    </p>
    
    <h2>Do sitemaps really work?</h2>

    <p class="mb-25">
        Yes sitemaps work. Especially when you're website is new. Sitemaps help Google better crawl your entire website instead of you having to manually request every individual page.
    </p>
    <h2>Where do you place sitemaps?</h2>

    <p class="mb-25">
        <p>You can always specify the path to a sitemap but the best place to put them is in the root folder of your website.</p>
        <p>Most crawlers look in the root directory.</p>
    </p>
